        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 3:44PM EDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM EDT/244 PM CDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm near Campbellsville, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Campbellsville, Knifley, Feathersburg, Romine, South Campbellsville,
Wrights, Elk Horn, Mannsville, Wooleyville, and Acton.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
